$version Hand-crafted DE10-Nano per-bit fixture $end
$comment 8 LED bits, 4 switch bits, 2 button bits, HDMI out pixel data, accelerometer sample bus, and 8 ADC channels — all as INDIVIDUAL per-bit / per-channel signals (no vector buses). Tests the auto-bind service's per-bit fallback tier and exercises the LED / switch / button / ADC slot families. $end
$date 2026-05-04 $end
$timescale 1ns $end
$scope module top $end
$var wire 1 ! led_0 $end
$var wire 1 " led_1 $end
$var wire 1 # led_2 $end
$var wire 1 $ led_3 $end
$var wire 1 % led_4 $end
$var wire 1 & led_5 $end
$var wire 1 ' led_6 $end
$var wire 1 ( led_7 $end
$var wire 1 ) sw_0 $end
$var wire 1 * sw_1 $end
$var wire 1 + sw_2 $end
$var wire 1 , sw_3 $end
$var wire 1 - key0 $end
$var wire 1 . key1 $end
$var wire 24 / hdmi_out_data $end
$var wire 36 0 accel_xyz $end
$var wire 12 1 adc_ch_0 $end
$var wire 12 2 adc_ch_1 $end
$var wire 12 3 adc_ch_2 $end
$var wire 12 4 adc_ch_3 $end
$var wire 12 5 adc_ch_4 $end
$var wire 12 6 adc_ch_5 $end
$var wire 12 7 adc_ch_6 $end
$var wire 12 8 adc_ch_7 $end
$upscope $end
$enddefinitions $end
$dumpvars
